  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense. It involves making illegally-obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or other crimes) appear to come from a legitimate source. This process typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement (introducing illegal money into the financial system)\n2. Layering (concealing the source through complex transactions)\n3. Integration (making the money seem legal)\n\nMoney laundering is illegal in most countries and can result in:\n- Significant prison sentences\n- Large fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n\nFinancial institutions and businesses are required to report suspicious transactions to help prevent money laundering.",
